mnist = tf.keras.datasets.mnist

(x_train, y_train),(x_test, y_test) = mnist.load_data()
x_train, x_test = x_train / 255.0, x_test / 255.0

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape=(28, 28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.2),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')
])

model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=5)
model.evaluate(x_test, y_test)

Modeling 시작¶

Learning rate = 0.1¶

1) Hidden Layer = 1, Hidden Node = 8, learning rate = 0.1

In [30]:
# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models
from tensorflow.keras import layers

# tf.set_random_seed(2021) <-  tensorflow 1 version
tf.random.set_seed(2021)

# 1 #
model1 = models.Sequential() # ANN 
model1.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model1.add(layers.Dense(1)) # Output layer - regression node 1

# 2 #
# loss function optimizer 
adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.1)

# 3 #
model1.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='mse', metrics=['mape'])

#   #
es = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, restore_best_weights=True) # Early stopping
lr = tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.1, min_lr=0.001) # learning rate 


# 4 #
# model.fit(train_data, train_targets, epochs=80, batch_size=16)
reg_history1 = model1.fit(train_features, train_target, epochs=300, batch_size=1024, validation_split=0.2,
                       callbacks=[es,lr])

# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models
from tensorflow.keras import layers

# tf.set_random_seed(2021) <-  tensorflow 1 version
tf.random.set_seed(2021)

# 1 #
model2 = models.Sequential() # ANN 
model2.add(layers.Dense(16, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model2.add(layers.Dense(1)) # Output layer - regression node 1

# 2 #
# loss function optimizer 
adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.1)

# 3 #
model2.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='mse', metrics=['mape'])

#   #
es = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, restore_best_weights=True) # Early stopping
lr = tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.1, min_lr=0.001) # learning rate 


# 4 #
# model.fit(train_data, train_targets, epochs=80, batch_size=16)
reg_history2 = model2.fit(train_features, train_target, epochs=300, batch_size=1024, validation_split=0.2,
                       callbacks=[es,lr])

# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models
from tensorflow.keras import layers

# tf.set_random_seed(2021) <-  tensorflow 1 version
tf.random.set_seed(2021)

# 1 #
model3 = models.Sequential() # ANN 
model3.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model3.add(layers.Dense(16, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model3.add(layers.Dense(1)) # Output layer - regression node 1

# 2 #
# loss function optimizer 
adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.1)

# 3 #
model3.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='mse', metrics=['mape'])

#   #
es = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, restore_best_weights=True) # Early stopping
lr = tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.1, min_lr=0.001) # learning rate 


# 4 #
# model.fit(train_data, train_targets, epochs=80, batch_size=16)
reg_history3 = model3.fit(train_features, train_target, epochs=300, batch_size=1024, validation_split=0.2,
                       callbacks=[es,lr])

# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models
from tensorflow.keras import layers

# tf.set_random_seed(2021) <-  tensorflow 1 version
tf.random.set_seed(2021)

# 1 #
model5 = models.Sequential() # ANN 
model5.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model5.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model5.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model5.add(layers.Dense(1)) # Output layer - regression node 1

# 2 #
# loss function optimizer 
adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.1)

# 3 #
model5.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='mse', metrics=['mape'])

#   #
es = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, restore_best_weights=True) # Early stopping
lr = tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.1, min_lr=0.001) # learning rate 


# 4 #
# model.fit(train_data, train_targets, epochs=80, batch_size=16)
reg_history5 = model5.fit(train_features, train_target, epochs=300, batch_size=1024, validation_split=0.2,
                       callbacks=[es,lr])

# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models

model6.add(layers.Dense(16, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model6.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))

# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models
from tensorflow.keras import layers

# tf.set_random_seed(2021) <-  tensorflow 1 version
tf.random.set_seed(2021)

# 1 #
model7 = models.Sequential() # ANN 
model7.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model7.add(layers.Dense(1)) # Output layer - regression node 1

# 2 #
# loss function optimizer 
adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=1)

# 3 #
model7.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='mse', metrics=['mape'])

#   #
es = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, restore_best_weights=True) # Early stopping
lr = tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.1, min_lr=0.001) # learning rate 


# 4 #
# model.fit(train_data, train_targets, epochs=80, batch_size=16)
reg_history7 = model7.fit(train_features, train_target, epochs=300, batch_size=1024, validation_split=0.2,
                       callbacks=[es,lr])

# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models
from tensorflow.keras import layers

# tf.set_random_seed(2021) <-  tensorflow 1 version
tf.random.set_seed(2021)

# 1 #
model14 = models.Sequential() # ANN 
model14.add(layers.Dense(16, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model14.add(layers.Dense(1)) # Output layer - regression node 1

# 2 #
# loss function optimizer 
adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001)

# 3 #
model14.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='mse', metrics=['mape'])

#   #
es = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, restore_best_weights=True) # Early stopping
lr = tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.1, min_lr=0.001) # learning rate 


# 4 #
# model.fit(train_data, train_targets, epochs=80, batch_size=16)
reg_history14 = model14.fit(train_features, train_target, epochs=6000, batch_size=1024, validation_split=0.2,
                       callbacks=[es,lr])

# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models
from tensorflow.keras import layers

# tf.set_random_seed(2021) <-  tensorflow 1 version
tf.random.set_seed(2021)

# 1 #
model15 = models.Sequential() # ANN 
model15.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model15.add(layers.Dense(16, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model15.add(layers.Dense(1)) # Output layer - regression node 1

# 2 #
# loss function optimizer 
adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001)

# 3 #
model15.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='mse', metrics=['mape'])

#   #
es = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, restore_best_weights=True) # Early stopping
lr = tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.1, min_lr=0.001) # learning rate 


# 4 #
# model.fit(train_data, train_targets, epochs=80, batch_size=16)
reg_history15 = model15.fit(train_features, train_target, epochs=6000, batch_size=1024, validation_split=0.2,
                       callbacks=[es,lr])

# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models
from tensorflow.keras import layers

# tf.set_random_seed(2021) <-  tensorflow 1 version
tf.random.set_seed(2021)

# 1 #
model16 = models.Sequential() # ANN 
model16.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model16.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model16.add(layers.Dense(1)) # Output layer - regression node 1

# 2 #
# loss function optimizer 
adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001)

# 3 #
model16.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='mse', metrics=['mape'])

#   #
es = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, restore_best_weights=True) # Early stopping
lr = tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.1, min_lr=0.001) # learning rate 


# 4 #
# model.fit(train_data, train_targets, epochs=80, batch_size=16)
reg_history16 = model16.fit(train_features, train_target, epochs=6000, batch_size=1024, validation_split=0.2,
                       callbacks=[es,lr])

# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models
from tensorflow.keras import layers

# tf.set_random_seed(2021) <-  tensorflow 1 version
tf.random.set_seed(2021)

# 1 #
model17 = models.Sequential() # ANN 
model17.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model17.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model17.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model17.add(layers.Dense(1)) # Output layer - regression node 1

# 2 #
# loss function optimizer 
adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001)

# 3 #
model17.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='mse', metrics=['mape'])

#   #
es = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, restore_best_weights=True) # Early stopping
lr = tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.1, min_lr=0.001) # learning rate 


# 4 #
# model.fit(train_data, train_targets, epochs=80, batch_size=16)
reg_history17 = model17.fit(train_features, train_target, epochs=6000, batch_size=1024, validation_split=0.2,
                       callbacks=[es,lr])

# Network  
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import models
from tensorflow.keras import layers

# tf.set_random_seed(2021) <-  tensorflow 1 version
tf.random.set_seed(2021)

# 1 #
model18 = models.Sequential() # ANN 
model18.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model18.add(layers.Dense(16, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model18.add(layers.Dense(8, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(train_features.shape[1],)))
model18.add(layers.Dense(1)) # Output layer - regression node 1

# 2 #
# loss function optimizer 
adam = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001)

# 3 #
model18.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='mse', metrics=['mape'])

#   #
es = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, restore_best_weights=True) # Early stopping
lr = tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.1, min_lr=0.001) # learning rate 


# 4 #
# model.fit(train_data, train_targets, epochs=80, batch_size=16)
reg_history18 = model18.fit(train_features, train_target, epochs=6000, batch_size=1024, validation_split=0.2,
                       callbacks=[es,lr])

1layer끼리 비교¶

In [175]:
%matplotlib inline

R_squared = performance_1layer['R_squared']

plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'Malgun Gothic'
plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 12

plt.figure()

x = np.arange(len(index_1layer))

plt.bar(x-0.0, R_squared, label='R_squared', width=0.7, color='#f26b5b')
plt.xticks(x, index_1layer)

plt.legend()
plt.xlabel('models')
plt.ylabel('performance')
plt.ylim(0, 1)
plt.title('R-squared')

plt.show()

plt.close()
